data.name: labelX3.Text
data.value: The Gauge Control will send Entry and Leave events when any Pointer crosses a given boundary. This can be seen by moving any of the below gauge pointers - either manually or by selecting the "Auto" button.

data.name: labelX13.Text
data.value:
Each Pointer can be monitored in order to update external components and/or to limit or constrain the selected pointer value.
The Star Pointer to the left is being tracked and constrained to only be permitted to enter the "Good" or "Excellent" areas of the scale.

data.name: labelX39.Text
data.value:
Tooltip templates accept .Net Format Specifiers. Scale labels can also be displayed using these specifiers
The value range for the above scale is from 0 to 1, with the labels being displayed as a percentage via the '0%' format specification.

data.name: labelX36.Text
data.value:
Name - The Name of the GaugeItem.
StartValue - The starting Value (Range and Section items).
EndValue - The ending Value (Range and Section items).
Value - the Value of the item (Pointer items).
